International Minerals andChemical Corp said its board approved a 50-mln-dlr budget to bespent over the next several years to build productionfacilities for a newly developed product to be used to improvethe lean weight of hogs.    The new product, porcine somatotropin (PST) is described asa natural bio-synthetic protein that improves the lean weightand rate of weight gain, as well as reduces the cost of feedfor market hogs, the company said.    Specific details of the PST production project, includingsites for the proposed facilities and engineering plans, werenot disclosed.    International Minerals said it set a completion target forthe spring of 1989, by which time necessary Food and DrugAdministration approvals are expected to be obtained. Reuter&#3;